.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-EXPERIMENT" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.2.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-experiment \- Aggregate, tag, and annotate one tracked run
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose experiment [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Work with a single tracked run's record. `show` is a read\-only aggregation: scheduler status, the post\-run efficiency score, the artifact manifest, and submit\-time provenance in one object, contacting the scheduler only as much as `status`/`score` already do (squeue, terminal\-only sacct/sstat). `tag` and `note` attach labels and timestamped observations to the tracked record; they contact no scheduler and rewrite only that record. Nothing here submits, cancels, exports, or opens a connection.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
\fBshow\fR
Show one tracked run aggregated into a single object. See hpc\-compose\-experiment\-show(1).
.TP
\fBbundle\fR
Write a reproducibility bundle for one tracked run. See hpc\-compose\-experiment\-bundle(1).
.TP
\fBtag\fR
Add or remove short labels on a tracked run. See hpc\-compose\-experiment\-tag(1).
.TP
\fBnote\fR
Append a timestamped note to a tracked run. See hpc\-compose\-experiment\-note(1).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB-v\fR, \fB--verbose\fR
Increase diagnostic verbosity; repeat for debug\-level logs.
.TP
\fB--debug\fR
Enable debug\-level diagnostics (equivalent to \-vv unless RUST_LOG is set).
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--offline\fR
Forbid SSH, remote delegation, Slurm scheduler contact, submissions, allocations, and cancels.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
